    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1609"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1609">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/115.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Blocker</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Eagle Pass</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegram January 31, and despatch 1013, I have agreed to certify
                    invoices of coal mined by Constitutionalists at Rio Escondido mines provided
                    coal is consigned general manager of company, who advised consulate this company
                    has entered into agreement with Constitutionalists whereby Constitutionalists
                    will deliver limited amount of coal from company’s mines to Rio Escondido
                    Company at Eagle Pass, Texas, in lieu of payment to Constitutionalists a normal
                    sum for same. Have seen agreement between both parties and believe they are
                    acting in good faith as agreement does not affect the company’s claim for
                    confiscation of their mines against the Mexican Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blocker.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
